HTML/CSS KBA REVIEW


What is a pseudo class?
	-A CSS pseudo-class is a keyword added to a selector that specifies a special state of the selected element(s). 
	For example, :hover can be used to change a button's color when the user's pointer hovers over it.

What precedence is given to css style (least to most)?
	-external -> internal -> inline

How to import a css file?
	-<link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="example.css" />

What are the 5 formats for using colors?
	-HEX, RGB, CMYK, HSV, HSL

How many instances of each id value can you have per document?
	-1, must be unique

How many instances of a class value can you have per document?
	-can be applied to many different tags, does not need to be unique

Does HTML display extra whitespace on the web page?
	-no, unless the text is surrounded by a <pre></pre> tag

In a css file, what does . and # represent?
	-# signifies and id, . signifies a class

What are the different position properties and what do they do?
	-relative
	-absolute
	-static
	-fixed
	-sticky

How do you comment in CSS?
	-/*This is an example of a comment*/

What is opacity?
	-a css property, opacity is the degree to which content behind an element is hidden, and is the opposite of transparency.

What is an <a></a> tag?
	-link tag
	-<a href="">Text that is clickable</a>

How to link to an anchor tag?
	<a href="#section2">Go to Section 2</a>
	<div id="section2"> The link would take you to this section of the page</div>


